main event: A bright, round object was observed in the sky over Oakland, California on August 25, 1966.
interesting points: The object was bright and steady, resembling a perfect circle.
The object did not move in any direction, but rather decreased in size and brightness until it disappeared.
The sighting lasted for approximately 2 hours and 43 minutes.
The observer compared the object's brightness to that of a blinking, flashing aircraft.
The observer drew a sketch showing the object's path, indicating it moved quickly and then descended.
sighted object: a bright, round object in the sky
photographs: yes, but the negatives were underexposed and unable to be analyzed
